question: What are genes related to Distal renal tubular acidosis?
agent_answer:
The genes related to Distal renal tubular acidosis are:

1. [SLC4A1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:11027)
2. [ATP6V1B1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:853)
3. [ATP6V0A4](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:866)
4. [WDR72](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:26790)
5. [FOXI1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:3815)

These genes are associated with the development or progression of Distal renal tubular acidosis.
